Nollywood actress, Funke Akindele, has reiterated her decision to have the latest evicted housemate of the 2019 Big Brother Naija ‘Pepper Dem’ edition, Diane, feature in her television drama series, Jenifa’s Diary. Diane was evicted on Monday night following random selection by veto power holder, Frodd. Funke had on September 2 visited the housemates and expressed her desire to have Diane join the drama crew. WE LOVE YOU DIANE. WE ABSOLUTELY LOVE YOU NO MATTER WHAT!!! TEAMDIANE ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️ A post shared by  _Official Diane BBN4_ 🇳🇬 (@diane.russet) on Sep 30, 2019 at 11:41am PDT Commenting on a post made by Diane’s Instagram handlers after her eviction on Monday, the 42-year-old said the crew cannot wait to have her join them. “We can’t wait to have you onboard #jenifasdiary we love you,” she said. Big Brother Naija 2018 second runner-up, Tobi Bakre, has already joined the cast of Jenifa’s Diary. Source: Qed